description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_klick-out.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_thefinalcrash02.wav
tags: hi-tech meachanical mutate button crash alien cyborg destroy switch soundesign electro robot processing transform clack click noise glitch fx slices soundeffect effect digital cuts

description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_thefinalcrash01.wav
tags: robot processing hi-tech button computer crash alien cyborg switch soundesign electro transform clack click mutate noise glitch fx slices soundeffect effect digital cuts

description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_kick-it04.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

contributors_browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/42.0.2311.90 Safari/537.36
description:
Recording of the power supply fan and the CPU fan of my old Gateway computer (currently my sound studio) through the slot where my CD drive should go...
I recorded this sample with a Telex/Boston mic (not a good buy by the way) with a small cloth bag over the mic head to muffle the high freq noises. I ran the recording through Audacity and cut it up and then passed it through a 31 Band EQ VST plugin in FL Studios 3 and i removed the high freq sounds and boosted the mid tones. 

This sample is intended for willy313 to be used in his upcoming computer game "Sub Zero Conditions: 2" as the loop for either a robot or the ambient sounds for the game levels, but use it if you like it.
name: engineorbunker loop.wav
tags: mechanic noise background machine bunker ambient ambience engine computer fan szc2

I ran the recording through Audacity and cut it up and then passed it through a 31 Band EQ VST plugin in FL Studios 3 and i removed the high freq sounds and boosted the mid tones. 

This sample is intended for willy313 to be used in his upcoming computer game "Sub Zero Conditions: 2" as the loop for either a robot or the ambient sounds for the game levels, but use it if you like it.

description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_kickbox02.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

The samples are random, I'm afraid. The box was playing 'Hickory Dickory Dock', but you'll have a hard time reconstructing it.

tags: clockwork wind wind-up machine piano short toy music-box fisher-price melodic chime

It's completely handmade and consists of a bunch of analog circuitry that when powered creates strange oscillations in current. It's also built into a Seseame Street toy saxophone. This set sounds like a robot talking. If chopped up and sequenced you could do a lot with it.

contributors_browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/43.0.2357.65 Safari/537.36
description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_hihat-open02.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

contributors_browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/43.0.2357.81 Safari/537.36
description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_ad-vocator.wav
tags: transform clack click hi-tech mutate processing soundesign switch button slices noise cuts digital effect fx glitch soundeffect
